Last-minute holiday cookie addition: lemon ricotta cookies! So fluffy and cloud-like♥️ These aren’t on my site yet, so I’ll put the recipe here:
4 ounces butter
3/4 cup sugar
lemon zest
1 egg
1 cup ricotta 
1 tsp vanilla
2 tsp lemon juice 
1.25 cups flour
1 tsp baking powder
1/4 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp salt
Frosting:
1.5 cups powdered sugar
lemon juice

1. Beat together soft butter and sugar. 
3. Add lemon zest, egg, ricotta, vanilla and lemon juice.
4. Sprinkle flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt on top. Stir to combine; chill overnight.
5. Bake 2-teaspoon sized balls of dough at 350 for 12 minutes, until lightly golden brown underneath.
6. Let cool; whisk together powdered sugar + lemon juice to make glaze.
7. For garnish: take small pieces lemon zest, boil in sugar water until soft, dip in lemon juice and roll in sugar.
